## Known Issues
- **Apostrophe in project path:** The path "Claude's Home" contains an apostrophe which can cause glob/search failures in subagents. When delegating file searches to subagents, ensure paths are properly quoted or escaped.

See `memory/` for detailed profiles and context.

## CLI Tools (ch) — prefer over Read/Edit for tasks & memory

Install once: `cd cli && npm link`. Then use `ch ...` from anywhere, or `./ch ...` from repo root.

| Operation | Command |
|-----------|---------|
| Dump active tasks (JSON) | `ch tasks dump --active --json` |
| Add a task | `ch tasks add "<title>" [--section todo] [--priority medium]` |
| Move task to section | `ch tasks move <id> <section>` |
| Mark done | `ch tasks done <id>` |
| Update title/note/priority | `ch tasks update <id> --title "..." --note "..." --priority high` |
| Next available id | `ch tasks next-id` |
| Validate tasks.json | `ch tasks lint [--fix]` |
| Markdown snapshot | `ch tasks export --md` |
| Person fields | `ch mem person <slug> [--field slack_id,email] [--json]` |
| Fuzzy person lookup | `ch mem whois "<name>"` |
| Memory index (JSON) | `ch mem index --json` |
| Session digest | `ch context [--json]` |
| List pending gaps | `ch gaps list` |
| Resolve a gap | `ch gaps resolve <n>` |

**Rules:**
- NEVER read `tasks.json` or `TASKS.md` directly — always use `ch tasks`.
- NEVER `ls memory/people` to check existence — use `ch mem person exists <slug>` or `ch mem whois`.
- `ch` enforces unique ids — do not guess the next id; call `ch tasks next-id`.
- If `CH_HOME` is unset, the CLI walks up from cwd to find the repo root automatically.

## Dashboard
- **Run with:** `node serve.js` (from project root) — opens at `http://localhost:3000/dashboard/`
- **Tasks now live in `tasks.json`** (not TASKS.md). The dashboard reads and writes JSON; `ch tasks export --md` gives a markdown snapshot.
- Memory files (people, projects, glossary) remain Markdown in `memory/`.
- Tasks poll every 2s for changes — edits via `ch` or Claude Code appear automatically.
- **FS-Access caveat:** users who previously opened a `TASKS.md` FileSystem handle must re-pick `tasks.json` once in the dashboard (the old handle is stale).

### Dashboard Architecture
- `dashboard/js/main.js` — entry point, imports all modules, config loading
- `dashboard/js/tasks-parser.js` — parses markdown tasks (also used by `ch tasks export`)
- `dashboard/js/tasks-board.js` — board view rendering, drag-drop, inline card editing
- `dashboard/js/tasks-list.js` — list view rendering
- `dashboard/js/memory-renderer.js` — memory tab rendering (overview, files, directories)
- `dashboard/js/memory-parser.js` — parses memory markdown files (fields, tables, sections)
- `dashboard/js/memory-modal.js` — modal CRUD for people/projects pages
- `dashboard/js/inline-edit.js` — inline editing for context page (fields, table cells, section lines)
- `dashboard/js/http-loader.js` — HTTP fetch/save fallback (httpSave, loadMemoryViaHttp)
- `dashboard/js/state.js` — shared state, tab switching, status bar
- `dashboard/js/persistence.js` — IndexedDB handle storage for FileSystem API
- `dashboard/js/overview.js` — overview tab widgets
- `dashboard/js/theme.js` — dark/light theme toggle
- `dashboard/styles/` — base.css, tasks.css, memory.css, modal.css, overview.css, misc.css
- `serve.js` — Node.js dev server with `/api/save` (POST) and `/api/memory-manifest` (GET)

### Task Priority System
- Priorities: `low` (blue), `medium` (yellow), `high` (red) — default is `medium`
- Stored in `tasks.json` as `"priority": "medium"` on each task object.
- Board shows clickable priority dots — click cycles low → medium → high
- Notes use em-dash separator: `**Title** — note text`
